FT  25 MAY 93 / ITC set to clear Tyne Tees TV
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Independent Television Commission will today give Yorkshire-Tyne Tees
Television a clean bill of health on how the merged ITV region is being run.
The commission launched a formal investigation after Ms Ann Clwyd, the
shadow heritage secretary, complained that Tyne Tees was in effect being run
by Yorkshire from Leeds and was being destroyed 'as an autonomous and
independent broadcaster'.
The commission, which has sought to preserve the autonomy of Tyne Tees with
its own separate regional licence, is happy with both the business and
programme commissioning structures now in place.
But it warns that it will continue to monitor the performance and to ensure
that there are no moves towards unacceptable integration at Yorkshire-Tyne
Tees, in which Pearson, owner of the Financial Times, has a significant
stake.
Ms Clwyd had argued that the destruction of Tyne Tees as an autonomous
broadcaster 'demands an urgent and decisive response from the ITC'.
