<TEXT>
THE House of Lords yesterday approved a government move to allow employers
to pay higher salaries to non-union members. Ministers had moved to change
the law, after a Court of Appeal judgment earlier this month, that it was
unlawful for workers to be offered financial incentives to give up union
membership.
