<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAY 93 / People: Sweetmeats for Whitehead
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Having amassed a long string of advisory positions at blue chip companies
across Britain since his retirement from the diplomatic service last summer,
Sir John Whitehead, the former ambassador to Japan, has now topped up his
collection with a non-executive directorship at Cadbury Schweppes.
Cadbury's chairman Sir Graham Day retired recently as did non-executive
director Richard Hornby, and the beverage and confectionery company says
that the combination of Whitehead's 'experience in international affairs and
his specific Pacific Rim region expertise' made him a suitable addition to
the board. The Pacific Rim last year accounted for 13 per cent of group
sales and 14.5 per cent of operating profits.
But Whitehead is already a senior adviser to Morgan Grenfell, an adviser to
Inchcape, Cable &amp; Wireless, and Guinness as well as to the president of the
Board of Trade and the Welsh Development Agency. How does Cadbury Schweppes
think he will find the time to make a worthwhile contribution? 'I would cite
the example of Sir Graham Day' a spokeswoman rejoins. 'He was an extremely
effective chairman but also a very busy man. It can work well.'
</TEXT>
