<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAY 93 / CBI urges faster settlement of bills
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MEASURES to speed the payment of bills by large companies to thousands of
small suppliers were proposed yesterday by the Confederation of British
Industry.
The CBI said small businesses are estimated to be owed more than Pounds 100m
in overdue debts at any one time. It urged large companies to declare their
payment policies in annual reports rather than give a detailed calculation
of the average time taken to settle bills as urged by the Department of
Trade and Industry.
Mr Richard Brucciani, CBI smaller firms council chairman, said: 'The problem
of late payment requires a change of culture and attitude in business, and a
published statement of corporate payment policy would give suppliers a
useful insight into this.
'It would also expose directors to scrutiny and provide a basis on which
they and their auditors could be tackled for poor payment practices in
breach of their stated policies.'
